text: @GOP @maziehirono @brianschatz @TulsiGabbard @SenateDems I know that nobody will read this, but I need to vent for a second. Today’s false alarm in Hawaii was scary, yes. I cried with my children in the closet while texting my husband that we love him...saying our goodbyes.

And guess what? I don’t hate North Korea. I bet the families there are just as scared as we are (maybe even more). There’s a NK mom over there, just like me, worried sick about keeping her two small kids safe from harm. To their leader, she is an abstract. Insignificant.

But you know what’s even scarier? The realization that this very well could have been real. And it might be real tomorrow. Or next week. And Trump doesn’t care. This is all an ego trip for him. Our lives are abstract to him. We don’t matter to him.

So I beg you all, on behalf of my six year old and my four year old, please stop the madness. Stop the hateful rhetoric that amplifies tension. We are real families in real danger, and we need you to step up and speak out. There has to be a peaceful path. Please.
IMO I think this false alarm was a good thing. It shows who is actually prepared or not if the real thing actually does come.
